name: Bruce Keebaugh
bio: Founder , The Big Group, Hospitality Agency

social_posts.post_text:
Happy Bday to the best of the best !! Nothing like a trip to the 2 dollar shop to “chic erfy” the Chyka !!!

Anyone out and about today, Chyks will be wearing her pink “Birthday Girl” badge all day !!!!

I love you baby, have the BEST day @chykak and welcome to 54 ( or 45) - it’s a pretty fun age 🤩

Well good bye 2022 from the Happiest ( and today the wettest) place on Earth @disneyland , with our little family all together again, which makes me the Happiest Man on Earth !!!

Thank you to everyone for making 2022 such a great year and here’s to a ripping 2023. Who knows what it will bring, but we will do it together, side by side, laughing and knowing that nothing can get in the way of a good time - even rain at Disneyland !!!

New Years Day in LA, doing Runyon with BJ…

Great way to start 2023 - I kind of love a New Years Day, it’s like fresh school books, re set, a re start, new dreams and aspirations ……life is for living!!

Interesting News today - 3 years ago our major events industry was shut down, without hope or future, and very little recognition of our economic & cultural impact to society.

Thank you Peter Rolfe @newscorpaus @heraldsunphoto 

A major call out and congratulations to each and every player who has survived, served , cooked, sung, kicked & danced, built stages tents and more , driven patrons, secured sites, made hotel beds, cleaned bathrooms and taken out the rubbish at the end !!!

Events are back, Melbourne is coming back, and now we must re build our reputation as the Global Events Capital - via innovation, ongoing govt capital investment and most importantly education. 

Victoria must have a Hospitality Institute, specialising in educating event specialists that feed into our nations workforce, built and operating by 2025, that’s my goal.

Over and out …
Today @chykak and I went to The Museum of the Future in Dubai - simply extraordinary, set in 2071 it focuses on opportunities, hope and innovation. Magnificent

So great to be back in the Middle East, especially our favourite place, the sandpit ( the desert )

Camels, falcons, archery, dune bashing and the best sunsets #onlyindubai🇦🇪 @babalshamshotel

Life is a bloody fun ride ….last month our family psychic ( yes we do have one !! ) rang at the end of the February and said March was going to be crazy busy, full of travel, work opportunities & events so she felt I needed to watch my “energy” levels ….at time I thought she was off base as the months diary then look normal…..

In the last three and half weeks I have flown on separate trips to Singapore, Thailand , the Middle East for work and play. Four trips to Sydney including settling @chykak and I into a new apartment up there for work.

@thebiggrouphospitalityagency have pitched for business, tendered for contracts, created amazing events and the team are walking into a weekend of Formula One in our events capital of Melbourne.

Bloody Great !! It’s so good to be busy and doing what we do so well - creating great experiences

I am about to zoom down to Main Ridge for a weekend to festigammo for BK55 ….when Chyks rang to see if I could pick up a little posie of flowers ( hello that’s a massive bunch ) and then realised I had no clothes , hadn’t unpacked and forgot to get a shave 🪒!!!

So what’s the takeaway - thanks Mr Covid, you taught me a lot, we live a big life, and I bloody love it, busy people get stuff done & Pam ( our futurist) you were spot on !!!

#workhardplayhard #lifestooshort #nevercomplainsometimesexplain #italsotakesavillage

Well that really was fun…..BK55 ( and it’s not even my bday until next week !! )

Thank you @thebiggrouphospitalityagency it is really is handy having your own events co 😉

When I was One,
I had just begun.
When I was Two,
I was nearly new.
When I was Three
I was hardly me.
When I was Four,
I was not much more.
When I was Five, I was just alive.
Now I am 55 and thank god I’m alive 
And I maybe old, but I'm as clever as clever,
So I think I'll be 55 now, for ever and ever.

A.A Milne x Bruce Patrick Patrick Keebaugh 

Disclaimer- outfit NOT chosen by me, vintage 1972, I was 4 , thus outfit and the outcome speak for themselves!! 

#clothesmaketheman

When Otto’s happy - @chykak and I are happy ….

He came
He saw
He meet some of the real dogs of Potts Point ….and 

He’s happy - and he really loves the view !!

Sydney- here we’ve landed !!! Now it’s time to get to work ( and sorry GG I missed that zoom - way too many boxes 📦)

@thebiggrouphospitalityagency NSW2024

Someone wise said to me the other day - “we work hard to bring them up, to be strong, independent and ready to take on the world, but the problem is, they bloody go off and do it !!!”

Good luck our beautiful boy, fly close to the sun, and enjoy everything this next stage has to offer, but alway keep a check on the wings, my Incarus !!

I could not be prouder of all you achieved, and I will miss having my best mate around the corner but London’s calling …..

(So now it’s USA:1 , UK:1 ………Otto don’t even think of trying out for Best on Show at the World Dog Expo !!)

location.city_name: Four Seasons Resort The Nam Hai, Hoi An, Vietnam

social_posts.post_text:
Remoting 2023 commences in beautiful Vietnam 🇻🇳, bring it on ….

( sorry for the sunshine shots in advance)
Well hello London - we’ve missed you !!!!

Happy 29th Bday to my beautiful, spirited & smart daughter, Chessie ….have the best time in Mexico 🇲🇽 with your friends this weekend, we love you so much and miss you more than words can describe.

Love Dad
(#currentlynotbannedfrominsta)

From one donkey to another….Mucking around Marrakech and I couldn’t be happier. I’ve missed this crazy town, it’s beautiful people and the best Riad around @elfennmarrakech 

Happy Days

Well it’s not everyday, the woman you bumped into in Dubai over a decade ago, also named Chica ( not two for the price of one - but definitely extra fun) , invites you for an amazing birthday party weekend at Arundel Castle @arundelcastleuk.

A seriously fun and funny weekend as guests of the Duke and Duchess of Norfolk, lovely @eddienorfolk & the beautiful @chicanorfolk .

As Aussies we historically miss a lot due to the one part young nature and the other our amazing yet historically ancient land, but to stay as a house guests, in the oldest functioning castle in the United Kingdom, full of every original Canaletto, Van Dyke, precious Chinoiserie, silverware, porcelain, armoury & furnishings all lovingly restored and protected for future generations to share and enjoy, is extraordinary.

The gardens alone, also available for viewing are extraordinary- a massive undertaking for Eddie and his family, notwithstanding he is also Earl Marshall and has orchestrated HRH The Queen’s funeral and HRH King Charles and HRH Queen Camilla’s coronation - and more importantly he does a bloody good BBQ lunch !!!

Thanks you two - much love B&C

( oh and the company wasn’t bad either !!! )

Well London that was fun - BJ all set up and running in his new job, Chyks happy, a weekend party and now I’m back on the big bird to Oz, to juggle some plates for a very special project with @thebiggrouphospitalityagency !!!

Who knew the colour purple represented wisdom, creativity, royalty & luxury, and as @steffdalberto taught me, it’s one of the hardest colours in the world to create….

Anyway, it’s never been my thing, to the point where @thebiggrouphospitalityagency team don’t wear purple to work as it kind of drives me nuts 

Today I learnt to “lean into lilac” and bring a little colour purple to my life - thanks @flowersvasette
Never gets dull #onlyinparis - bring on today ,,,it’s a perfect day for a party !!!

Paris is always the ultimate party place…..

@thebiggrouphospitalityagency

Wedding over……so One Night in Paris with our besties 

Best men and each others weddings 
 Best mates for over 45 years 
Best night in Paris with our bestest other halves ….

#onenightinparis

One night only in “Roma with the Richo’s” ( post three hours sleep and an early early flight from Paris ) drinks at our hotel rooftop @sixsensesrome , soooo good, dinner @dalbolognese ( thanks @distasiocitta ) like beyond the best and then ….bed time with @chykak , much needed sleep before we head to the Italian countryside for RnR ….

This old boy needs a rest !!!!

So cruel to send this to my Melburnian brothers and sisters in arms, currently freezing in the winter cold ….but it’s pretty bloody nice to be starfishing around Casa Olivi in Marche, Italy..

#happydays

Happy long lazy days at beautiful @casaolivetta with my favourite son

#puglia

I am so proud of @chessiekeebaugh , her work ethic, acumen and career accomplishments, initially @chandeliercreative in NYC, and now of course in her LA days with the iconic @flamingo_estate .

Hard work pays off, and whilst she and her partner were to be sunning their days away with our family in Puglia, work comes first, and what a bloody brilliant brand activation this is .

A disused East Hampton motor repair mechanics from the 50s gets bought to life by @mytheresa.com & @flamingo_estate …genius, fresh and perfectly placed in the heartland of any New Yorker’s “in summer” residence. I love seeing two brands with minimal  bricks and mortar retail presence , showing globally the  power of exciting “temporary retail eventing”, aligned to brilliant storytelling and rich content to share - food, fashion & fast cars !!!
What could possibly go wrong!!!! 

Love it all - and as will all projects, I know a massive team has pulled this together, but I’m a super proud Dad of my girl….well done sweetheart, important to celebrate the big milestones 💚 ( now get to that sales floor and sell sell sell, and get to those media , and tell, tell, tell !!!! 😜)
Boat, float and soak….ing up that Italian sunshine & rosè with mio caro, Perfetto -vivere la dolce vite italiana

Well that’s was a busy week in London - @thebiggrouphospitalityagency meetings , event venue searching, stadia visits and a lot of cultural institution dinning - I’ve learn a lot . But the best of it was having time with my favourite son now based in London !!! ( oh and @spursofficial won !!!)
Well London, that was fun….sad to say goodbye to beautiful Abbi and B, but @chykak and I are now off for an adventure somewhere new !!!

It’s always great to find somewhere new, and ( thanks to Ned) we came across @mamulaisland near Kotor Bay, Montenegro, which is for me, a very particular traveler, and a seeker of great global hospitality, it’s very very good.

Egyptian businessman Samih Sawiris bought the entire island, a former fort & prison and has turned into the most elegant, chic boutique hotel within this geographically naturally beautiful location I’ve seen. It’s the perfect way to experience Montenegro.

Location aside, the design detail of the rooms, public spaces, gym, spa, beach etc is so well done

But for me it’s always about the food, the people and the business culture- and this is rich in every way. The food is only local, the staff engaging, warm and friendly and the management team are across every detail 

It’s a big tick from me, and I’m hard to please!! Oh and added for the cynics, I don’t do “pay to say” , rather I always “pay to stay” !! 

#janettaandkevinarehappy

Well what a night for our beautiful friend @carolyncreswell for her #cc50vis - black tie dinner in an fort on top of the hills of Vis, magic!!!

 ( apart from the @chykak slight slow start due to a wardrobe malfunction seeing her whole dress put into a bucket of water five minutes to kick off - it was a bloody amazing night, show goes on !!)

From one caterer to another, this woman Edwina Thompson @edthomson_art has done THE most brilliant job for our combined mate @carolyncreswell #cc50vis - thanks for being Ed authentic, artistic, genuinely creative and fun ( just don’t try and copy my beach wear !!! )

So excited for the finale Riviera party tomorrow, then it’s home for a big @collingwood_fc Grand Final win and @thebiggrouphospitalityagency smashing out the start of the season and a massive Grand Final week !!!

I cannot tell you how proud I am of this entire team @thebiggrouphospitalityagency who worked tirelessly this week to support @collingwood_fc and @afl with corporate hospitality, sponsor breakfast lunches and dinners, members events, family days and players parties. 

After all these years to share in this glorious moment for Melbourne was incredible/ but people are everything, and  every TBG full time member of staff from finance to reception and IT, we’re there, side by side doing whatever we could as a Big Group team to support our operations and front of house teams create great outcomes for our customers.

I’m so proud and so happy - thank you

Oh and @kate.langford if you ever decide a career change - videographer might be your jam ( but hopefully not as you do CEO very well !! )

Well my darling, just as beautiful today, as on this day 31 years ago…I found the VHS of our wedding and couldn’t not share it !!!!

What a ride we have had, who knew when we drove out the St Paul’s Cathedral gates what lay ahead - our beautiful babies @bj_keebaugh and @chessiekeebaugh , our business baby @thebiggrouphospitalityagency and all the other businesses, travel , highs and lows and everything in between !

We’ve done it all together, climbed the mountain, crossed the rivers , changed and grown, always hand in hand. I couldn’t do it without you.

Happy Anniversary my darling 

B

Thank you @leonardjoelauctions for donating to one of my favourite charities, @movember - it was fun to have you join me at my weekly barber 💈 appointment with Paz @kingsdomainbarbers Prahran, to chat the forthcoming timepiece auction at Leonard Joel Monday 23rd October at 4pm

WARNING - sorry to preach, but had to express an opinion, it’s only my opinion, which you may not agree with, but that’s kind of the point I suppose !! 

If you choose to comment, please do that with respect of others in mind.

Well @ngvmelbourne that’s was bloody amazing!! Thank you @vogueaustralia and the creative team @gloss.creative you really know how to make magic and bring joy, art aside ….no one loves a Carpark party more than me!!
And it was great to see @chykak semi cruchless ( oh and the triennial..next level and well worth a visit )

What an amazing few weeks we have had….last week @thebiggrouphospitalityagency hosted a 33 year re union for all past full time team members. 

First time in a long time that I’ve been to a cocktail party for a few hundred guests and  known every persons name !!! 

It was very special to connect, laugh and share so many wonderful stories.

As Big Group scales up for a very BIG 2024, ( much news soon to come) , it’s so important to look back at the hard work & commitment of so many who stood side by side, making, creating , laughing and crying as we grew up together within our Big Group Family.

Thank you to everyone who made that happen - I’ll never forget it. 

Bruce 

( oh and if anyone has any great old behind the scenes TBG photos  from the 90s, 2000s, 2010 era we would love them for the book, “By Invitation Only”, which will be released Q3, 2024

Well that’s Christmas wrapped up with a Big, Big Group bow…I cannot thank our @thebiggrouphospitalityagency team for all they do, amazing food, service and the holy grail of cleaning up!! Thank you Andrea, Lucinda , Sarah , Noah & Jeremy so much . And to our sponsor @chykak HOME, not only are you charming, witty , beautiful and fun…but your plates , knives , forks, napkins, & crackers all from @harrisscarfe make for a pretty fancy Christmas setting. 

And to top off the day - having our beautiful @chessiekeebaugh home with her partner Maurice, was our Christmas Miracle!!! 

I hope everyone enjoyed this years Wetmas as much we did with our family & friends ……but always thinking of our @bj_keebaugh and his darling Abbi over the seas together !!

Now let’s stay in bed & eat scraps all day and play with our gifts 🎁

What a year ….full of planes, parties and automobiles. 

Started the year with very bad “long” hair 1/1/23 in downtown LA, but this year is going to end on a massive high in the heart of Sydney, with better hair!!

We have laughed, cried and celebrated so much this year. I have a lot to thank 2023 for, and I’m very excited and grateful for all the amazing opportunities in 2024, with @chykak by my side , our beautiful babies in far away lands, we will grow and scale @thebiggrouphospitalityagency with the team. There are new venues to open, new retail to create, contracts to mobilise , a book to launch and a new market sector to play in, a renovation to start and finish and who know what else will pop up along the way - but that’s how we like it , a glorious happy circus of never ending surprises, that we navigate for 365 days ….thats a year in motion.

Tomorrow I officially go zero alcohol….who knows where that will take me, but the plan is optimum health - fit , fresh and ready to take on more challenges in 2024! Happy New Year to everyone and I hope you make your dreams come true, and that we have a more peaceful 2024 globally.
Founder , The Big Group, Hospitality Agency
